obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40658)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and duration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40658&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National`
  line `Capital Territory of Delhi Laws (Special Provisions) Second Act, 2011.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the National Capital Territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the 1st day of January, 2012.`
  line
  line `(4) ^1[It shall cease to have effect on the 31st day of December, 6`
  line `[2026]], except as respects things`
  line `done or omitted to be done before such cesser, and upon such cesser section 6 of the General Clauses Act,`
  line `1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply as if this Act had then been repealed by a Central Act..`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2021, s. 4, for "It shall cease to have effect on the 31st day of December, 2020" (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 2023, s. 4, for "2023" (w.e.f. 24-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40659)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40659&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "building bye-laws" means bye-laws made under section 481 of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957) or the bye-laws made under section 188, sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 189 and sub-section (1) of section 190 of the Punjab Municipal Act, 1911 (Punjab Act 3 of`
  line `1911), as in force in New Delhi or the regulations made under sub-section (1) of section 57 of the`
  line `Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), relating to buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) "Delhi" means the entire area of the National Capital Territory of Delhi except the Delhi`
  line `Cantonment as defined in clause (11) of section 2 of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957`
  line `(66 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(c) "encroachment" means unauthorised occupation of Government land or public land other than`
  line `streets, lanes, footpath and parks, by way of putting temporary, semi-permanent or permanent`
  line `structure for residential use or commercial use or any other use;`
  line
  line `(d) "local authority" means the Delhi Municipal Corporation established under the Delhi`
  line `Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957), or the New Delhi Municipal Council established`
  line `under the New Delhi Municipal Council Act, 1994 (44 of 1994) or the Delhi Development Authority`
  line `established under the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), legally entitled to exercise control`
  line `in respect of the areas under their respective jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `^1[(e) "Master Plan" means the Master Plan for Delhi as notified under the Delhi Development`
  line `Act, 1957 (61 of 1957);]`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "punitive action" means action taken by a local authority under the relevant law against`
  line `unauthorised development and shall include demolition, sealing of premises and displacement of persons or their business establishment from their existing location, whether in pursuance of court`
  line `orders or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(h) "relevant law" means in case of--`
  line
  line `(i) the Delhi Development Authority, the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(ii) the Municipal Corporation of Delhi, the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957`
  line `(66 of 1957); and`
  line
  line `(iii) the New Delhi Municipal Council, the New Delhi Municipal Council Act, 1994`
  line `(44 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(i) "special area", shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (vi) of regulation 2 of the`
  line `Building Regulations for Special Area, Unauthorised Regularised Colonies and Village Abadis, 2010`
  line `notified in the Gazette of India vide S.O. 97(E), dated the 17th January, 2011;`
  line
  line `(j) "unauthorised development" means use of land or use of building or construction of building`
  line `or development of colonies carried out in contravention of the sanctioned plans or without obtaining`
  line `the sanction of plans, or in contravention of the land use as permitted under the Master Plan or Zonal`
  line `Plan or layout plan, as the case may be, and includes any encroachment.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used but not defined herein shall have the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act,`
  line `1957 (66 of 1957) and the New Delhi Municipal Council Act, 1994 (44 of 1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40660)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Enforcement to be kept in abeyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40660&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any relevant`
  line `law or any rules, regulations or bye-laws made thereunder, the Central Government shall before the`
  line `expiry of this Act, take all possible measures to finalise norms, policy guidelines, feasible strategies and`
  line `make orderly arrangements to deal with the problem of encroachment or unauthorised development in the`
  line `form of encroachment by slum dwellers and Jhuggi-Jhompri clusters, ^1*** unauthorised colonies, village`
  line `abadi area (including urban villages), and their extensions, existing farm houses involving construction`
  line `beyond permissible building limits and schools, dispensaries, religious institutions, cultural institutions,`
  line `storages, warehouses and godowns used for agricultural inputs or produce (including dairy and poultry) in`
  line `rural areas built on agricultural land, as mentioned below:--`
  line
  line `(a) orderly arrangements for relocation and rehabilitation of slum dwellers and Jhuggi-Jhompri`
  line `clusters in Delhi in accordance with the provisions of the Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board`
  line `Act, 2010 (Delhi Act 7 of 2010) and ^2[the Master Plan] to ensure its development in a sustainable,`
  line `planned and humane manner;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(c) orderly arrangements in accordance with the provisions of the National Capital Territory of`
  line `Delhi (Recognition of Property Rights of Residents in Unauthorised Colonies) Act, 2019 (45 of`
  line `2019), the National Capital Territory of Delhi (Recognition of Property Rights of Residents in`
  line `Unauthorised Colonies) Regulations, 2019 and the regulations for village abadi area (including urban`
  line `villages) and their extensions as per the following cut-off dates:--`
  line
  line `(i) for unauthorised colonies as provided in the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `(Recognition of Property Rights of Residents in Unauthorised Colonies) Regulations, 2019;`
  line
  line `(ii) for village abadi area (including urban villages) and their extensions as existed on the 31st`
  line `day of March, 2002 and where construction took place even beyond that date and up to 1st day of`
  line `June, 2014;]`
  line
  line `(d) policy regarding existing farm houses involving construction beyond permissible building`
  line limits;
  line
  line `(e) policy or plan for orderly arrangement regarding schools, dispensaries, religious institutions,`
  line `cultural institutions, storages, warehouses and godowns used for agricultural inputs or produce`
  line `(including dairy and poultry) in rural areas built on agricultural land and guidelines for redevelopment`
  line `of existing godown clusters (including those for a storage of non-agricultural goods) required to cater`
  line `to the needs of the people of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(f) orderly arrangements in respect of special areas in accordance with the Building Regulations`
  line `for Special Area, Unauthorised Regularised Colonies and Village Abadis, 2010 within overall ambit`
  line `of Master Plan in force; and`
  line
  line `(g) policy or plan for orderly arrangements in all other areas of the National Capital Territory of`
  line `Delhi in consonance with the Master Plan on its review.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (1) and notwithstanding any judgment, decree`
  line `or order of any court, status quo--`
  line
  line `(i) as on the 1st day of January, 2006 in respect of encroachment or unauthorised development;`
  line
  line `^5[(ii) in respect of unauthorised colonies identified under the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `(Recognition of Property Rights of Residents in unauthorised Colonies) Regulations, 2019, in respect`
  line `of village abadi area (including urban villages) and their extensions, which existed on the 31st day of`
  line `March, 2002, and in aforesaid categories, where construction took place up to 1st day of June, 2014,`
  line `as mentioned in sub-section (1);]`
  line
  line `(iii) in respect of special areas as per the Building Regulations for Special Area, Unauthorised`
  line `Regularised Colonies and Village Abadis, 2010; and`
  line
  line `(iv) in respect of all other areas within the National Capital Territory of Delhi as on the 8th day`
  line `of February, 2007,`
  line `shall be maintained.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, it is hereby clarified that any development`
  line `approved by the competent authority or the local authority under the relevant laws and the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, including repairs permissible under the building bye-laws in force, shall`
  line `continue to remain permitted.`
  line
  line `(3) All notices issued by any local authority for initiating action against encroachment or`
  line `unauthorised development in respect of areas referred to in sub-section (1), shall be deemed to have been`
  line `suspended and no punitive action shall be taken ^6[till the 31st day of December, ^7[2026] ], if--`
  line
  line `(a) it is constructed prior to the dates specified for different areas as enumerated in`
  line `sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(b) it conforms to the safety standards as in force or such other safety requirements as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(c) it complies with the directions with respect to safety, if any, issued by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case punitive action is required to be taken by any local authority, prior approval of`
  line `the Administrator of the National Capital Territory of Delhi or the officer authorised by him in this`
  line `behalf, shall be obtained by the authority or officer concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding any other provision contained in this Act, the Central Government may, ^8[at any`
  line `time before the 31st day of December, ^7[2026] ], withdraw the exemption by notification in respect of`
  line `encroachment or unauthorised development mentioned in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "hawkers and urban street vendors," omitted by Act 32 of 2017, s. 5 (w.e.f. 31-12-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 2021, s. 6, for "the Master Plan for Delhi, 2021 " (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (b) omitted by Act 32 of 2017, s. 5 (w.e.f. 31-12-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 2021, s. 6, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 2021, s. 6, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "till the 31st day of December, 2020" (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 42 of 2023, s. 5, for “2023” (w.e.f. 24-12-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "at any time before the 31st day of December, 2020 " (w.e.f. 29-12-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40661)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Provisions of this Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40661&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `During the period of operation of this Act,`
  line `no relief shall be available under the provisions of section 3 in respect of the following encroachment or`
  line `unauthorised development, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) encroachment on public land except in those cases which are covered under clauses ^1`
  line `[(a) and`
  line `(c)] of sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) removal of slums and Jhuggi-Jhompri dwellers, ^2`
  line `*** unauthorised colonies or part thereof,`
  line `village abadi area (including urban villages) and their extensions in accordance with the relevant`
  line `policies approved by the Central Government for clearance of land required for specific public`
  line projects.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "(a), (b) and (c)" (w.e.f. 31-12-2017).`
  line
  line `2. The words "hawkers and urban street vendors," omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-12-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40662)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40662&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, from time`
  line `to time, issue such directions to the local authorities as it may deem fit, for giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and it shall be the duty of the local authorities, to comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40663)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Validation of acts done or omitted to be done, etc., during 1st January, 2012 up to the date of enactment of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878&sectionId=40663&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00026_201120_1517807326878
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of any court, all`
  line `things done, or, omitted to be done, and all action taken, or, not taken, during the period beginning on`
  line `or after the 1st day of January, 2012 and ending immediately before the date of enactment of this Act,`
  line `shall, in so far as they are in conformity with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done,`
  line `or, omitted to be done, or, taken, or, not taken, under these provisions as if such provisions were in`
  line `force at the time such things were done or omitted to be done and action taken or not taken during the`
  line `aforesaid period.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
